<br>
When this thread was first started, I asked my guild to respond calmly and intelligently, if at all. I do realize this is the Blast Furnace, and NOT a place for shiny happy thoughts. That being said, I will try to take my own advice and stay cool. <br>
There were only 6 people that know exactly what happened that evening in Velks. I trust Zed and the members that were there - if they weren't happy with the cleric, then it just wasn't meant to be. Zack could be the best cleric on the server, but if the group doesn't click, it doesn't click. I can not say who was right or wrong, or indeed if anyone was in the wrong, since I, like most of you, was not there. I don't want to get into the debate on when to CH and who should pull. I'm a bard - I pull - I have never been in a group with a cleric that pulls, and I don't CHeal. I personally don't care who pulls, as long as the whole group is on the same page and it works. This point is now moot, everyone group will do it how they wish. <br>
As I hear the story, he was not asked to leave for a guild cleric, since she wasn't even on that continent at the time, but again, that is now a moot point. <br>
What disturbs me more is the KC incident. Having trusted my life to Minah repeatedly, I find it hard to believe she would leave mid battle &quot;without warning&quot;.  I have known Minah (and many other Dark Rain members)  to be late to guid events while waiting for a replacement to come to the pick up group. Please understand I am not saying you are lying, I just feel I am missing part of the story here. <br>
As far as the leadership of Dark Rain:<br>
Ventrixx (SK formerly known as Venerial Owns)  - GuildMaster<br>
Bemeni - GuildMistress<br>
Relic - Officer<br>
Zedicuss - Officer<br>
Bustyn  - Officer<br>
Please feel free to contact one of us in game if you wish to discuss this, or any other matter further. Dark Rain does NOT condone this type of behavior, and it's my hope to not be a flame topic again <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
(But, on a side note, at least they spelled our name right)<br>
 <p>Bemeni Zanobia<br>
Rockstar<br>
