<br>
Just thought I'd respond here.  We were grouped for what, maybe an hour or so, I'd say?  Fun group, lots of banter, really chatty, even if pulling was a little slow.  Not much we could do to fix that, since everything was camped in the zone, but we did pretty well.<br>
<br>
I was in KC to hunt with Kreig yesterday, I'd promised him that I was going to hang out with him, he was a little down, and I was there to cheer him up.  When the new group formed, I was upset with him for disbanding without warning our group, but I'd made a promise to him, and he asked me to go with him.  One second, we were fighting, the next second, Kreig had disbanded, and he sent me a tell saying that he needed me with him in the other group.  The leader of the new group was spamming me with tells and invites, and I told him to hang on, we were in the middle of a pull, and I couldn't leave right away.  He said that was cool, and that they'd wait for me for a minute.<br>
<br>
I told the group that I had to go to take care of Kreig, and that I was sorry, and when the message went through to the group, Punk was pulling.  I disbanded from the group at that time so that I wouldn't suck up the group's xp, and I stayed with Punk's group, keeping him on target and casting heals on him until the mob was dead.  I didn't move to join the other group until they were finished fighting the mob that Punk had pulled, because I wanted to make sure that they were safe before I left.<br>
<br>
I was just as frustrated with the situation as everyone else, and I would have been perfectly happy to stay with Punk's group, but I'd made a promise to Kreig, and I wasn't going to walk away from him at that time, he was very down, and needed a friend with him.  I apologize to Punk and the rest of the group, but I was stuck between a rock and a hard place, and had a split second to make a judgement call on that one.  And I did give the group warning that I was leaving, I realize it was quick notice, but I did let y'all know that I was disbanding, and stayed with you to make sure that you were ok.  If that makes me a bitch, then oh well, not much I can do about it.  Sorry you feel that way, bud.<br>
<br>
-Minah<br>
